
Instructions to collect descriptors from largescale DFT runs from qball
This assumes fully separated

MAKE SURE "RedirectFolder" and "RunName" are identical between all .py!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

1.Set RunName, TopDataFolderSpeeds, XPosVals, ZPosVals, and assumedOrbitals in CollectDFTData-qball.py

2. Run CollectDFTData-qball.py

3. Set RunName, TopDataFolderSpeeds, XPosVals, and ZPosVals in CollectTDDFTEnergies-qball.py

4. Run CollectTDDFTEnergies-qball.py

5. Set RunName in MakeCrystalGraphRep-TDDFT-fullySeparated.py

6. Run MakeCrystalGraphRep-TDDFT-fullySeparated.py

7. Set RunName in MakeCoulombMatrixAndCrystalRep-fullySeparated.py

8. Run MakeCoulombMatrixAndCrystalRep-fullySeparated.py



To get full time dependence run:

@. Set RunName, numPrevious (number of previous time steps), and OrbitalToUse (target quantity) in MakeCombinedDescriptors-qball-fullySeparated.py

@. Run MakeCombinedDescriptors-qball-fullySeparated.py

@. Set RunName, numPrevious, OrbitalToUse, and CalculationType in MakeCombinedDescriptors-CombinetheSeparated.py

-> full data file















